    "body": "Problem: `:write ++patate foo` doesn't error out, instead it turns on mkdir_p and uses \"atate foo\" as the filename. Same with ++edit. The parser just does strncmp without checking what comes after.\r\n\r\nSolution: require the next char after the option name to not be a letter or digit. \r\n\r\n",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-22T08:43:08Z",
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Looks fine, but a bit inconsistent with how `++(no)bin(ary)` is checked, as they instead terminate on `!ASCII_ISALPHA` via `checkforcmd` (for better or for worse... :grin:)\r\n\r\nE.g: `:e ++bin6` is accepted (6 is used as the fname), but `:w ++p6` is not here.\r\n\r\n(Also, as `++edit` is from Vim, I assume Vim has the same problem?)",
            "created_at": "2026-04-17T07:54:31Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39146#issuecomment-4266316491",
